I just brought my wife home from giving birth. The staff from top to bottom are very enthusiastic and professional, absolutely do not accept compensation (when I leave the hospital, I send some fruit and they happily accept it). Insurance covers up to 80%, but for items that are not covered, the cost is relatively high (my wife gave birth naturally and spent more than 7 million, choosing a 2-bed room). If you take the time to browse around and see if it's not crowded, you should choose a room with 3-4 beds to save money, because a room with many beds is still spacious and comfortable, with curtains covering each bed to ensure privacy. There is a canteen and mini supermarket in the hospital, but you should buy all the supplies and bring them with you, because the prices here are 1.5-2 times the prices outside.

I have covid. The day after taking the fever reducer, my lower abdomen had cramping pain. Because it's close to home, I went to this hospital for emergency treatment. After briefly asking about my symptoms and that I was suffering from covid, they transferred me to the isolation room, where the hospital bed was full of insects. Then they gave me painkillers, took blood and sent me for an ultrasound. Waited 30 minutes for the ultrasound results, and the blood test results were not available until the end of swallow season. After 2-3 hours I had a fever again. I also think they sent blood samples to SG for testing. After that, they informed me to wait for the medicine. At this time, I had a fever and had no strength left. They made me wait another hour to get the medicine to take home. I had a high fever while lying in a room full of insects, with the fan turned on at maximum without any blankets. Maybe the medicine is imported from Western countries so we can wait until Russia and Europe are out of war before importing it. Is this a serious emergency, doctors at large private hospitals? And this is not the first time, before my mother went to the emergency room and I spent my youth just waiting for the results and filing documents. There are not many illnesses, but there are many documents to file. I advise everyone to not go to this hospital if they have any serious or mild illness. Severe cases can cause death, but mild cases can become serious. Horrifying, horrible experience.

(Including surgery fee 300, hemostasis of tooth socket 100, and examination fees + blood tests, x-rays) - Hospital fees are gone: 518k, health insurance pays 414k, I pay 104k A total of 600k for the tooth. Reduced costs compared to external extraction, provided enough medicine (pain reliever and 2 types of antibiotics), quick and easy way of working. _ I'm just wondering what the hospital fees include, I don't see it declared in the invoice. The room was clean, my tooth was easy to pull out so only the assistant pulled it out. 5-10 minutes is all done, no pain at all. Don't be afraid of dentistry. The room has 2 surgical chairs. There is Dr. RHM CKI in charge. The first day was a bit painful because the anesthetic ran out, but just take the medicine as prescribed and you'll be fine. After the 2nd and 3rd day, everything is ok. _ The tour guide is quite professional. If you don't know anything, don't be shy. Although we will also meet this person and that person, everything is good on the day we go. The hospital is very clean, the medical staff is very polite, the doctor is very professional and always gentle with patients as in his language the word hospitable is, no other hospital in Binh Duong is like this place because When we are sick, our body is very tired and easily irritable and emotional, so just one impolite gesture will easily make the patient angry or feel sorry for themselves, so with the staff's friendly style, The doctors and nurses make this place feel like home. So patients come here very comfortably and heal quickly. Even the cleaning lady was very gentle, neat, tidy and behaved very kindly and politely. This is truly the brand of Hoan My Van Phuc Hospital. I remember one time when I took my baby to the hospital for treatment and was told that he was admitted to the hospital because he had a fever. Then the nurses made an appointment to examine him at 2:00 p.m. It was Sunday, but at exactly 2:00 a.m. a doctor came but the baby was sleeping. The doctor gently said, "Children have a hard time sleeping, you can come back for a check-up later." I was very touched by the kindness the doctor had for my baby and everyone else. Right in the medicine dispensing room is the slogan: "We understand that the best medicine comes from the doctor's heart" and many other slogans like in the emergency room,... It must be said that the hospital does the right thing. Do what they propose wholeheartedly and don't just talk about it. In addition, it is a private hospital but will still waive parts of health insurance. In addition, there will be fees but the price is affordable, not expensive and worth the money the patient spends.

When lying in bed, the service is very dedicated, just press the button at the head of the bed and a nurse or doctor will come. with a caring and warm attitude. I really hope that Binh Duong will have such hospitals with reasonable prices that are affordable for patients in difficult circumstances. In general, I am very satisfied with the name Van Phuc.

I see that many people have given this hospital many bad reviews. I have insurance at this hospital and from my experience of having been to the hospital many times, this hospital is much better than other hospitals. I have had internal medicine examinations. , ear, nose and throat, eye, and dermatology here are considered a lot, so I would like to summarize a little of my experience: - The attitude of the medical staff here is very enthusiastic and cheerful, from the security guard, the nurse to the doctor. When she first arrived, the lady at the procedure desk always greeted her from afar, very warmly, when she arrived. When I asked about the room, the ladies all gave me very enthusiastic instructions. When I asked the security guard, every doctor I met so far was enthusiastic, took the trouble to listen, and asked carefully about the patient. I have never met a doctor. Has a tense, unpleasant, or loud attitude. As soon as I peek outside the door, the doctor invites me to sit in a chair to wait for the examination. His attitude is very polite. Usually outside the clinic door, there will be a nurse sitting to do the procedure. very enthusiastic and enthusiastic guide, - Regarding the examination fee, the hospital calculates the insurance clearly without any fraud, the difference in examination cost is only a few dozen, while the examination process with endoscopy or ultrasound is a few dozen more. - In terms of hygiene, the hospital is very clean and airy, Let me tell you a little more about BV 512 so you can easily compare: - I went to buy medicine at pharmacies in Phu Chanh and Tan Uyen, everyone selling medicine said that this hospital sells expensive medicine. In fact, I was left to die once from the doctor to the pharmacy staff, it's like this. I had a sore throat and went to the doctor like a saint, opened my mouth and looked at the prescription, asked one more question, acted as if I was going through the motions, went out to buy medicine, the doctor prescribed the antibiotic clarithromycin 250mg, the nurse herself crossed out 250. took the pen in exchange for 500mg, arbitrarily increased the drug concentration but the quantity remained the same without asking my opinion. Another problem is that 1 such pill is sold outside for about 7-8 thousand, here it is sold for 13 thousand, I When I picked up the receipt, I found it rude, and there were a few girls who bought the medicine and cursed loudly, saying they had insurance but the hospital said they were out of medicine and told the patient to go out and buy it themselves. Who in the world would the hospital let it run out? From there, we can see what the 512-bed hospital is like. I haven't said how good or bad the quality of the doctors is, but in terms of medical examination and treatment attitude, Van Phuc Hospital is still better. Now, if the examination at Van Phuc Hospital doesn't improve, I will go down. Saigon will never examine 512 beds again. Well, this is already a long post, that's my experience, thank you for reading, cordial goodbye,
